<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1897-06-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1897-06-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="269" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d269">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">Julian
                                    Pauncefote</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Sherman</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">British
                                        Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1897-06-13"><hi rend="italic">June 13,
                                1897</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to your note, No. 652, of
                            the 27th of April last, giving the names of the United States revenue
                            steamers which will cruise in Bering Sea during the sealing season, I
                            have the honor, by direction of the Marquis of Salisbury, to inform you
                            that the sloop <hi rend="italic">Wild Swan</hi>, Commander Napier, and
                            the gunboat <hi rend="italic">Pheasant</hi> will be employed in Bering
                            Sea on patrol duties this season on behalf of Her Majesty’s
                            Government.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Julian
                            Pauncefote.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>